{
  "stem": "1062.4",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Then coming out from the sewer, I met this [INAUDIBLE] from [INAUDIBLE], who gave me this Tehillim to say to pray, you know?",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And when I finished the prayers, I looked out the window.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And there were huge tanks passing through, not in the camp, but below the camp.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Those are American tanks.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And we didn't know who it was, what it was, because I didn't even know America is at war.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Somebody said, the British are here, the British are coming, you know?",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "[LAUGHS]",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It reminds me of Paul Revere, you know?",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[LAUGHS] The British are coming.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But we didn't know the Americans-- Americans at the war.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And the tanks passed by.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But for some reason, two hours later there was everything in camp.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "There were conserves, you know, meats, what you used to keep in, in, in-- it was called conserves, you know?",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "In-- in-- in boxes.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Butter, honey, marmalade, frankfurters.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Like, I don't know, because what happened, the troops, when they passed by, they have to move on.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They dumped everything out of the, of the, of the tanks, whatever they had, their supplies.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And they were infiltered into the camps.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So we all started to eat.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "That night, more people died from overeating and eating this rich food than they died during the German occupation.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And the following morning, there were two American officers.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "They came through the gate of Buchenwald.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And I want you to know something.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Buchenwald, the streets were piled with dead, piled, like, like cork wood.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And people outside even the-- who was alive couldn't move anymore.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "They couldn't walk.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "They couldn't.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And when the two officers came through the camp and we came through the, the gate, they walked in through the Appellplatz.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They started to get into the camp.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
